git: version control
====================

git-scm.com

Pro git book: https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2

git config --global user.name "Ulf Swedin"
git config --global user.email "ulf@swedin.nu
git config --global push.default matching
git config --global alias.co checkout

Kommandon:

git init > .git

git status

git add .

git rm --cached -r node_modules

git commit -a -m "Initialize repo"

ssh:
=============
.ssh\id_rsa
id_rsa.pub

generate ssh

> ssh -keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "ulfswedin@gmail.com"


https://www.ssh.com/ssh/protocol/

Github:
=======

git remote add origin https://github.com/BagheeraBear/webserver2.git
git push -u origin master

c:\Curl\web-server>git remote
origin

c:\Curl\web-server>git remote -v
origin  https://github.com/BagheeraBear/webserver2.git (fetch)
origin  https://github.com/BagheeraBear/webserver2.git (push)

